{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-lesson-template-js","path":"/setup-expo","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>The fastest way to get started with React Native is to us Expo and run the app on your device. Feel free to use the <a href=\"https://reactnative.dev/docs/getting-started\">React Native docs</a> or <a href=\"https://docs.expo.io/versions/latest/\">Expo docs</a> for reference.</p>\n<h4 id=\"youll-need\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#youll-need\" aria-label=\"youll need permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>You'll need:</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>a computer (Mac, Windows or Linux)</li>\n<li>a smartphone (iPhone or Android)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"install-node\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#install-node\" aria-label=\"install node permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Install Node</h3>\n<p>First, make sure you have Node.js installed (10.0 or later). You can do this by opening a terminal and running <code class=\"language-text\">node -v</code>. If not you can install it <a href=\"https://nodejs.org/en/\">here</a>. There's usually two version to choose from, pick the one that says LTS (Long Term Support) after the version number.</p>\n<h3 id=\"install-expo\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#install-expo\" aria-label=\"install expo permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Install Expo</h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"sh\"><pre class=\"language-sh\"><code class=\"language-sh\">npm install -g expo-cli</code></pre></div>\n<p>This installs the expo cli globally. We'll be using this to create our new project.</p>\n<h3 id=\"create-the-project\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#create-the-project\" aria-label=\"create the project permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Create the project</h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"sh\"><pre class=\"language-sh\"><code class=\"language-sh\">expo init AwesomeProject</code></pre></div>\n<p>You'll be prompted to choose a template. Pick the 'blank' - we're starting from scratch!</p>\n<h3 id=\"run-the-project\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#run-the-project\" aria-label=\"run the project permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Run the project</h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"sh\"><pre class=\"language-sh\"><code class=\"language-sh\">cd AwesomeProject\nnpm start</code></pre></div>\n<p>Note that you can also use <code class=\"language-text\">expo start</code> or <code class=\"language-text\">yarn start</code> if you have yarn installed.</p>\n<h3 id=\"preview-the-app-on-your-phone\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#preview-the-app-on-your-phone\" aria-label=\"preview the app on your phone permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Preview the app on your phone</h3>\n<p>First, make sure that your phone is connected to the same WiFi network as your computer. This is really important!</p>\n<p>Next you'll need to install the Expo client on your phone. This is the native shell Expo provides that lets you get started without having the build the native app yourself. Go to the App Store or Play store, search for \"Expo\" and install it. You will also have to create an Expo account if you don't already have one (don't worry - it's free!).</p>\n<p>Finally, open the browser window that was opened when you ran the packages. See the QA code? If you're on Android, you can scan the code with your Expo app. On iOS, open the camera app to can the code. You will be prompted to \"open in Expo\".</p>\n<p>At this point you should see something like this:</p>\n<div style=\"width:250px;margin:0 auto;margin-bottom:20px\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 800px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/react-native-v2/static/751147afd0d8cb4aacf421567a57889e/55d53/expo-init.png\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 216.53333333333333%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"Expo hello world\" title=\"Expo hello world\" src=\"/react-native-v2/static/751147afd0d8cb4aacf421567a57889e/acfc1/expo-init.png\" srcset=\"/react-native-v2/static/751147afd0d8cb4aacf421567a57889e/59afc/expo-init.png 200w,\n/react-native-v2/static/751147afd0d8cb4aacf421567a57889e/a45af/expo-init.png 400w,\n/react-native-v2/static/751147afd0d8cb4aacf421567a57889e/acfc1/expo-init.png 800w,\n/react-native-v2/static/751147afd0d8cb4aacf421567a57889e/55d53/expo-init.png 1125w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span>\n</div>\n<p>And that's it! You're ready to start coding!</p>","frontmatter":{"path":"/setup-expo","title":"[Expo] Getting started with Expo","order":3}},"allMarkdownRemark":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":0,"path":"/intro","title":"Welcome"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":1,"path":"/react-native","title":"About React Native"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":2,"path":"/the-expo-debate","title":"Should you use Expo or plain React Native?"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":3,"path":"/setup-expo","title":"[Expo] Getting started with Expo"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":4,"path":"/setup-rn","title":"[RN] Getting started with plain React Native"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":5,"path":"/debugging","title":"Debugging"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":6,"path":"/intro-to-react","title":"Basic React Native components"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":7,"path":"/safe-area","title":"Safe Area"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":8,"path":"/styling","title":"Styling"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":9,"path":"/styling-exercise","title":"Styling Exercise üìù"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":10,"path":"/components","title":"Components"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":11,"path":"/lists","title":"Lists"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":12,"path":"/lists-exercise","title":"Lists Exercise üìù"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":13,"path":"/navigation-intro","title":"Navigation Into"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":14,"path":"/navigation-rn","title":"[RN] Adding navigation with plain React Native"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":15,"path":"/navigation-expo","title":"[Expo] Adding navigation with Expo"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":16,"path":"/adding-navigation","title":"Adding Navigation"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":17,"path":"/navigation-exercise","title":"Navigation Exercise üìù"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":18,"path":"/react-hooks","title":"useState, useCallback, useEffect"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":19,"path":"/network-requests-exercise","title":"Network Requests Exercise üìù"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":20,"path":"/forms","title":"Ove